A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a cluttered office desk overflowing with paper envelopes and letters spilling onto the floor, while a frazzled secretary in period-appropriate attire sits overwhelmed with her head in her hands. A massive mail sorting cabinet looms behind her with dozens of tiny compartments, some overflowing. The color palette features muted mustards, teals, and warm browns typical of mid-century advertising art. The scene captures the chaos of communication management with a nostalgic, slightly humorous tone. No text or writing visible on any papers or surfaces.
